description.narrative: UNICEFNepal responded to the humanitarian needs of the children, women and their families that arose from the COVID-19 pandemic’s second wave and natural disasters. The COVID-19 response reached 727,6711people (female, 371,112) including 304,000 children with health, WASH, nutrition, child protectionand education services. 27,787 people (female 14,171) including 11,000 children (5,511 girls) benefitted through humanitarian response following small-scale floods and landslides. UNICEF contributed to the;national and local level planning guideline, to make it risk-informed and child-sensitive. Nineteen municipalities updated child-sensitive local disaster and climate resilience plans, while 50 municipalities developed and implemented 50 COVID-19 preparedness response plan. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/01/2022
